act:
759057 THE NAVY (AMENDMENT) ACT, 2005
NO. 23 OF 2005 [ 23rd June, 2005.]
An Act further to amend the Navy Act, 1957.
BE it enacted by Parliament in the Fifty- sixth Year of the Republic of India as follows:-
968921 1Short title.- This Act may be called the Navy (Amendment) Act, 2005.
1137033 2 Amendment of section 3.- In section 3 of the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), for clause (16), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:- ' (16)" Officer" means a commissioned officer and includes-
872560 aa subordinate officer other than a petty officer;
1772572 ba commissioned officer re- employed as such;'.
554332 3 Amendment of section 79.- In section 79 of the principal Act, for the words" Provided further that", the following shall be substituted, namely:- " Provided further that in computation of the said period of three years, any time during which,-
360709 athe commission of the offence was not known to the person aggrieved by the offence or to the authority competent to initiate action, the first day on which such offence comes to the knowledge of such person or authority, whichever is earlier;
512698 bit was not known by whom the offence was committed, the first day on which the identity of the offender is known to the person aggrieved by the offence or to the authority investigating into the offence, whichever is earlier, shall be excluded: Provided also that where the institution of the prosecution in respect of an offence has been stayed by an injunction or order, then, in computing the said period of three years, the period of the continuance of the injunction or order, the day on which it was issued or made and the day on which it was withdrawn shall be excluded:
Provided also that".
169054 4 Amendment of section 94.- In section 94 of the principal Act, for sub- sections 1, (2), (2A) and (3), the following sub- sections shall respectively be substituted, namely:- " (1) The Central Government may impose on any officer below the rank of commander one or more of the following punishments, namely:-
289181 aforfeiture of seniority in rank of not more than twelve months;
291115 bforfeiture of time for promotion of not more than twelve months;
77701 cmulcts of pay and allowances.
560772 2The Chief of the Naval Staff may impose on any officer below the rank of commander one or more of the following punishments, namely:-
832904 aforfeiture of seniority in rank of not more than six months;
674657 bforfeiture of time for promotion of not more than six months;
1595034 cmulcts of pay and allowances.
721317 2AThe Flag Officer Commanding- in- Chief of a naval command may, subject to regulations made under this Act, impose on any officer below the rank of commander one or more of the following punishments, namely:-
980228 aforfeiture of seniority in rank of not more than three months;
404318 bforfeiture of time for promotion of not more than three months;
451779 csevere reprimand or reprimand;
1463338 dmulcts of pay and allowances.
276410 3The commanding officer of a ship may, subject to regulations made under this Act, impose on any subordinate officer one or more of the following punishments, namely:-
1276137 aforfeiture of seniority in rank of not more than three months;
632872 bforfeiture of time for promotion of not more than three months;
618455 cmulcts of pay and allowances.".
1820929 5 Amendment of section 133.- In section 133 of the principal Act, for sub- section (6), the following sub- section shall be substituted, namely:- " (6) Any document purporting to be a report, under the hand of-
170547 aany Chemical Examiner or Assistant Chemical Examiner to the Government;
96816 bthe Chief Inspector of Explosives;
1781178 cthe Director of Finger Print Bureau;
1778321 dthe Director of Haffkeine Institute, Bombay;
1476248 ethe Director, Deputy Director or Assistant Director of a Central Forensic Science Laboratory or a State Forensic Science Laboratory;
1774572 fthe Serologist to the Government, upon any matter or thing duly submitted to him for examination or analysis, may be used as evidence in any proceeding under this Act.".
1182094 6 Amendment of section 151.- In section 151 of the principal Act,-
1638634 ain sub- section (1), for the word, brackets and figure" sub- section (2)", the words, brackets and figures" sub- sections (2) and (3)" shall be substituted;
469025 bafter sub- section (2), the following sub- section shall be inserted, namely:- " (3) Whenever any offender is sentenced by a court- martial to a term of imprisonment, in pursuance of this Act, not being imprisonment in default of payment of fine, the period spent by him in civil or naval custody during investigation, inquiry or trial of the same case, and before the date of order of such sentence, shall be set off against the terms of imprisonment imposed upon him, and the liability of such offender to undergo imprisonment on such order of sentence shall be restricted to the remainder, if any, of the term of imprisonment imposed upon him.".
1065337 7Amendment of section 163.- In section 163 of the principal Act, in sub- section 1, clause (e) shall be omitted.
651267 8Insertion of new section 163A.- After section 163 of the principal Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:- " 163A. Provision relating to parole.- Where any person is tried under the provisions of this Act, the Central Government or the Chief of the Naval Staff or the Flag Officers Commanding- in- Chief of the Naval Commands may in the case of conviction either with or without conditions release the person on parole.".
1122157 9Amendment of section 176.- In section 176 of the principal Act, in clause (b), for the words" ten thousand rupees in value", the words" the prescribed amount not exceeding rupees one lakh in value" shall be substituted.
1480177 10Amendment of section 184.- In section 184 of the principal Act, in sub- section (2), after clause (q), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:- " (qa) the amount required to be prescribed under clause (b) of section 176;".
803930 11Omission of Chapter XXII.- Chapter XXII of the principal Act and the heading relating thereto shall be omitted. ----
T. K. VISWANATHAN,
Secy. to the Govt. of India.
